  "question": [
    "The magnetic field at the centre of a circular coil of radius R carrying current I is 64 times the magnetic field at a distance x on its axis from the centre of the coil. Then the value of x is"
  ],
  "choices": [
    [
      "$R/4$"
    ],
    [
      "$R\\sqrt{3}$"
    ],
    [
      "$4R$"
    ],
    [
      "$R\\sqrt{15}$"
    ]
  ],
  "correctAnswer": 2,
  "explanation": [
    "$B_{center} = \\frac{\\mu_0 I}{2R}$. $B_{axis} = \\frac{\\mu_0 I R^2}{2(R^2+x^2)^{3/2}}$.",
    "Ratio $64 = \\frac{(R^2+x^2)^{3/2}}{R^3}$.",
    "$(R^2+x^2)^{1/2} = 4R \\Rightarrow R^2+x^2 = 16R^2 \\Rightarrow x = \\sqrt{15}R$."
  ],
